The paper deals with distributed synthesis, which is a topic in computer science that involves the coordination of multiple processes or agents. The paper specifically focuses on asynchronous systems with causal memory, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses control games and Petri games, which are topics related to Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Programming Languages (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper involves decision-making and strategy development, which are topics related to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
